{{Quote|What's the matter, Till? Don't tell me a hotshot pilot like you is afraid of the Dreighton Triangle.|[[Jenn]]|audio=Jenn-RAII.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: Rebel Assault II: The Hidden Empire">''[[Star Wars: Rebel Assault II: The Hidden Empire]]''</ref>}}
The '''Dreighton Triangle''' was a region of space within the [[Dreighton Nebula/Legends|Dreighton Nebula]].

Following the [[Battle of Dreighton]] and massive fighting in the Dreighton Nebula in general during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] (which led to the mutual annihilation of both [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] and [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] forces deployed there), stories about [[ghost ship]]s and hauntings by the spirits of dead pilots began to spread among the general populace. Many believed that a ship entering the Dreighton Triangle would never be seen again.

This reputation in the general populace made the region the perfect cover for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[TIE/ph "Phantom" Multi-Role Stealth Starfighter/Legends|Phantom TIE project]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].

